<br>
This is probably going to get me seriously flamed, but I think it's worth saying anyway.<br>
<br>
I've been reading rant forums for a long time, even posted a few rants myself on the old EQ boards when I was a younger wizard. Pretty much any site that deals with wizard topics has one. And some concerns are valid: better mana regen would be nice; a higher damage cap would be nice; being able to get Concussion/Brain Bite at level 39 would be nice; a DD that does 2000 at level 59 or 60, not just to a few epic mobs in the game, but to any mob, would be nice and, I feel, appropriate. <br>
<br>
But after all the ranting, I'm happy being a wiz. No, I'm not 60 yet, so I don't know the woes of those last 11 levels. Maybe I'll hit 55 and retire to start a monk. But right now, life is good.<br>
<br>
I think the problem is that most people start a wiz expecting to do the most damage of any casting class in the game. We do if the fight is shorter than 15 seconds; after that, pet classes do. What most people don't realize is that to do more damage than we do already, the entire aggro system would have to be changed. You can't do more damage than your tank's damage + tank's taunting if you don't want to get hit (and any slack that concussion buys you). Pet classes get to do more in the long run because that aggro isn't directed at them. So if you want more damage, you're playing the wrong game, unless you like tanking. Reworking the whole aggro system would be practically impossible and would change the game so much that it wouldn't be the same game at all.<br>
<br>
Another problem with all the focus on damage is that many wizzes almost totally ignore their stuns. Markar's clash stuns for 8 seconds and does 200 damage. That's a good deal in my book. Combined with Tishan's clash you can come close to chain stunning. I was in Frenzy last night, and I stunned the entire fight, only nuking once at the end. The damage you can save your group is incredible with these stuns. Yeah, chanters get more stuns earlier than we do, but they also have a lot more to do in a fight, where we have the luxury of devoting our attention to that one mob. Use your utility spells; your cleric will love you, your tank will love you, and you'll be more useful.<br>
<br>
Then there's the issue of mana efficiency. I too would like to be a bit more mana efficient, but then again I have a chanter in my group in 99% of important situations. Casual soloing or grouping is... well, unimportant in my book. I can still get more experience soloing for an hour than most classes can get in a group all day. In deep excursions into hostile territory, when everyone *needs* the highest mana regen or everyone dies, if you don't have a chanter with you, you're dead already.<br>
<br>
Also, if you're low on mana and your group is at full health, DON'T NUKE! Let your cleric do their thing. Help them out with a stun here and there so they don't go from FM to OOM in ten seconds, and relax. Don't be a hero.<br>
<br>
Ok, now the dreaded topic: ports. I love my ports. Sometimes I gate around from continent to continent for no reason. I'm probably on of the few wizards that never charges for a port, either. If I have the time *and* I'm in the mood, I'll give you a port. That's maybe once or twice a day. I still turn down 90% of requests, even when they offer 100pp, or they say d00d I died in Oasis and I'm bound in qeynos, plz plz plz help me.<br>
<br>
Yes, in many situations people will take a res over an evac, and you could say that decreases their worth. But when some moron trains you, or your drunken tank pulls five right after your cleric says &quot;OOM!&quot; and your cleric has zero chance of living or camping, people want one thing: to get the hell out of there. I don't evac very much; maybe twice this month that I can think of. In that same time the local clerics have performed hundreds of resses. I still wouldn't give up my evacs. Not for a 2000dd, not for a wizard only clarity spell. A lot of wizards disagree on this point. That's just my opinion. Druids get evacs, nukes, dots, and healing spells. They're an uber class, no one's arguing about that. I still like my wiz better.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying our class couldn't use some tweaking. But other classes could, too. Rangers come to mind.<br>
<br>
If you're that unhappy with your wizard, play another class. That's a solution I know most wizards hate to hear, but let's be real here; if you hate your girlfriend/boyfriend, you dump 'em, even if you've put many months into the relationship (all of you married folks don't jump on me, it's just an example, heh<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). If you hate reading Bukowski, stop buying his books. If you hate hearing me say the class isn't that bad, read another thread ;p.<br>
<br>
Galliamius Barbarossa,<br>
