</TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/8/01 8:48:32 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An Un-Rant</span><hr size=1> As a level 55 wizard, I will say that you are correct in some ways, but incorrect in others.  I'll give you a bit of information about what you can expect from 51 through 55 since I've been dealing with the pain of it for long enough.  Corrections are welcome from any who disagree.<br>
<br>
51: Ok, you just got to 51, and you get this nice spell called draught of fire.  643 damage in 3 seconds feels amazing, all those interupts are gone, and on paper, this means you can do 1286 damage in 6 seconds, which is a nice little upgrade from Ice Comet, it's fire based, and the resist rate isn't too bad at all.  So, life seems good.  Spend some time and you get Atol's Spectral Shackles, and you now have a spell that works fairly well.  Many groups will accept you to replace that druid for snare duty.  Karnor's Castle is the best place in Kunark since the mobs don't have TOO many hit points and the experience is decent.  You will also find groups on many servers as a wizard in this zone, contrary to popular belief.  If there is room for you, you CAN find groups here.  A bit more time spent, and you get Tishan's Discord, a GREAT stun spell.<br>
<br>
52: You get your first lure spell, only does 640 damage, doesn't scale up.  Your draught spell from 51 does a whole 5 damage more per cast, while the mobs seem to have gotten an extra 200+ hit points from 51 to 52.  Lure also gets resisted by just about everything you'd want to use it on, so those spite golems in Hate will STILL resist 5 out of 6 casts(lure of fire at level 55 is only slightly better on these).  No additional damage this level.  But, manaskin will fully replace diamondskin, same reagent cost, and it has +1 mana/tick, which is nothing, but over time it's SOMETHING at least.  Now, the very big positive, Tears of Druzzil.  This spell will do 600 damage per wave, and if cast on a single mob, will do up to 1800 damage if all three waves hit.  It's magic based, and generally 2 waves will land.  Old Sebilis groups are hard to get, and Karnor's is still good experience at this level.<br>
<br>
53: Jyll's static pulse, 2 second PB AoE that does 495 damage.  All those green zones that used to be so annoying are now not even a problem.  A greenie jumps you, just cast this, and with a 2 second cast, it almost never gets resisted.  Aside from that, 53 doesn't hold anything.  Lure of frost still does only 640 damage, and draught of fire does 653 damage now.  Not too exciting, but it's better than getting interupted with a 6.3 second ice comet or rend cast.  KC is starting to get slow for XP at this point unless you move to hands or basement.<br>
<br>
54: Ok, an AC upgraded shield spell, and a magic based draught(voltaic draught), 658 damage on this one, same 3 second casting time and same 215 mana cost, magic based.  But, draught of fire does the same damage with the same exact stats.  Nothing to get excited about since mobs resist magic more than fire in 90 percent of all cases.  KC is really slow on XP now except hands or basement, so you begin to push for groups in OS, or if you are lucky, you may get into a Howling Stones group.  54 is a definate hell level, slow XP, and in general, it's not a lot of fun.<br>
<br>
55: Ok, a new lure, gets resisted a little less on certain mobs, more than on others, but in general, it's just fire based.  Same exact damage as our level 52 lure.   Draught of Jiva is the magic based draught, consider it like Voltaic draught, but it DOES interupt casting.  Same exact damage, cast time, and mana cost.  Improved invis from Velious is self only, but makes it less of a risk to run through certain zones like Kael.  Truesight is just a combination of chill sight and see invis.  It's nice, but nothing new.  OS begins to open up, you've hit level 55, so are a bit more accepted.  The places you will want are Ilis Jail or Myconid King since these are where the XP will be best.  These groups generally need to be selective about who they invite, since a single group member without the skills to work as a part of the group can and will get the group killed.  The next rain also comes at 55, but in OS, tends to get resisted more than Tears of druzzil.<br>
<br>
<br>
Some will note I've left the pillar spells out.  The reason is that except for AoE groups and &quot;green zones&quot;, the AoE spells arn't generally tolorated well in groups.  The mobs have a LOT of hit points, so crowd control is THE most important thing.  Now, one thing that many groups will appreciate is you risking yourself to save the cleric or enchanter in your group.  If you keep a skin up(manaskin, diamondskin, or steelskin), you can be confident enough that you can take a hit or two without getting in trouble.  Because of that, if you need to nuke-agro a mob to yourself to give the enchanter 10 seconds to cast a mezz, it's worth it.  Just remember to STOP casting, or switch to immobilize and concussion(for those who have it) to let the tanks get the mob back off you.<br>
<br>
<br>
Being a wizard means you need to use every bit of skill you have to not only stay alive, but to keep your group alive.  If you get into groups, and they see you helping with crowd control, snares, stuns, roots, and just working with your group, they not only mind if you sit out for a few mobs to med, but they appreciate you.  Just remember to tell them when you go under 20 percent mana because if you don't, and they pull a train without knowing it, they may expect YOU to evac when you can't.  Wizard group skill isn't easy, and learning what you can and can't do can take a LOT of practice.  Learning how to agro a mob just enough to have it agro you, but not so much that they can't get it off quickly is also critical.  Even at 55, there are a few times when I over-agro the mob, but thanks to concussion, the times are getting fewer and fewer.<br>
<br>
Final topic is Concussion.  This spell is CRITICAL at the higher levels.  At 54, when you run into problems getting groups(if you have that problem), that may be a good time to get a group together to get it.  My recomendation is to get a mage with CoH.  Duel the mage, and use gravity flux to get the mage to the top of the wall.  The mage can then CoH your whole group up, and the human skeleton camp is GREAT XP from 51 through 54.  Hell, you might want to do that camp just for the uncontested XP camp alone.  You will need a decent enchanter, but for a good XP camp, they generally won't object too much.<br>
<br>
<br>
Good luck.  The 50s are painfully slow, especially level 54, so the best thing is not to dwell on that pathetic 5 HP increase in damage per level, and just try to focus on working well in a group.<br>
